Shortly after he said it all here, he went and did it.
A small account of the seven significant findings of the Lost Interview:
About how he learned to run a business:
"For all the time in the business, I've always asked, "why are you doing this?" And the answers you always get are, "Oh, it's just like this."
No one knows why they do what they do, no one thinks very deeply in business.
