Replacing analogues with digital signals is one of the most important changes the world has seen in recent years.
The Supreme Court (JC) rejected the constitutional claims made by the Senate and the House of Representatives against the Presidential Decree, which is moving the so-called “ Digital Television” from 2021 to 2015, as the eight votes required for its annulment have not been obtained.
