The draft declaration, prepared by Minister Olga Sánchez Cordero, proposed that the decree be declared unconstitutional, since the regulation of the radio and television programme was a right established by law for the Federal Telecommunications Commission (Cofetel), in violation of the principles of hierarchical subordination and legislative reserve.
Only Salvidar, Jorge Mario Pardo, Marguerite Luna and Sánchez Cordero voted in favour of the project.
